part 2: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rYLBnKVlej0&t=377s

1.install node js-open cmd prompt
in cmd prompt type
node -v
npm install -g yarn (npm-node package manager)


2.open cmd prompt:
  npm install -g create-react-app(for the first time it wil install, after that it will update)

3.open visual studio code:
 terminal
 new terminal
 in that type:
  create-react-app appName
  create-react-app helloworld(it takes few minutes to install)

  after that type
  cd appName
  npm start
  when we type this browser will automatically open

4.in visual studio code:
 at left corner-in folder(which we have opened already)
 here my folder name is "ReactJS"
 here my app name is "helloworld"
 ReactJS-helloworld-src-app.js

 it has some code..we can replace the <div> section by our own code.

everytime we should start from step 3 (after installation).
